<br>
If you're doing wizzies and the necro, I'd recommend using the 49 fire pet (don't forget your torch).. the wizards cast 3 dd spells, lightning (magic based) cold, and fire based.. so your pet will full resist 1/3 of all their casts.  The wizzies and necro go down in 1 char and 1 Scar for full exp.  (They survive a total of about 10-15 seconds.. get them right as they pop and the wizzies can't cast shieldskin).<br>
If you're taking the wizzies and the guard.. go for 51 earth.. the guard hits pretty hard and is very magic resistant.  (Never been able to stick Malosi on him), and he partials char/Scar/SoS about 1 out of 5 times.  Depending on how often the guard resists, you may have to skip a guard and kill him every other 10 minutes, but this still results in a about a blue an hour or so for 3 mobs.<br>
<br>
Still haven't found a way to get full exp for all 4 mobs and med to full before rotation starts again without reclaiming pet.. good for exp.. bad when you run out of malachite.<br>
<br>
The rogue is just a nuke fest, and isn't really a good option to add to your rotation due to how much mana you burn killing him.  Good to kill while waiting for the wizzie/necro spawns to come available.<br>
<br>
Beware the dual wielding and SK guards though (ie. somebody gives them a weapon) They average 117x3 per round while dual wielding, not including kick, and tore through a high summoned level vocerate earth in about 10 seconds.  The SK guards HT (never been hit, but pet has) and cast engulfing darkness/fear.<br>
<br>
I'd recommend doing the lightstone quest in Sro to get faction up to at least indiff (hand 4 ls/gls to the smith, then have somebody invis you, and click give), then continue with the red wine quest in 3rd gate to get faction with the guards up.  This makes it a lot easier to take both wizards and the necro in one ten minute cycle.<br>
